<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05085</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING THE ESTABLISHMENT AND IMPLEMENTATION OF AGRIBUSINESS VENTURES ARRANGEMENTS (AVAs) IN AGRARIAN REFORM LANDS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to institutionalize...AVAs, particularly in agrarian reform areas, to promote productive and collaborative ventures between the private sector and the Agrarian Reform Beneficiaries (ARBs) and transform them into farmer-entrepreneurs as well as maximize distributed agrarian lands without compromising the farmers' tenure rights; Emphasizes the principle of agrarian reform and provides that AVAs should not be a threat to the ARBs' land rights but should give incentive to develop their lands and improve their productivity.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BAGUILAT, TEDDY JR. BRAWNER</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-02-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Alejano (096 2017-05-30)</td><td>2. Garcia (G.) (026 2017-09-19)</td><tr><td>3. Nieto (000 2018-03-05)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Recommendations submitted by the TWG on 2018-03-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-WAITING FOR THE SUBMISSION OF THE DAR AO  AND POSITION PAPERS FROM THE RESOURCE PERSONS.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Committee Report approved on 2019-02-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-CR No. 9060</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB09060</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON AGRARIAN REFORM ON 2